6 An Act relating to the Insurance Department; amending
36 O.S. 2021, Sections 301, 1802, 1804, and 1805,
7 which relate to supervisors and conservators of
insurers; creating certain division within the
8 Insurance Department; defining terms; modifying
definitions; establishing certain powers for certain
9 supervisor; updating statutory language; establishing
certain powers for certain conservator; updating
10 statutory references; allowing the Insurance
Commissioner to employ or contract with certain
11 persons; establishing certain expenses as fixed by
the Commissioner; allowing the Commissioner to audit
12 certain persons or books; establishing certain
expenses as cost of administration; prohibiting
13 records to be considered certain records; prohibiting
disclosure of certain records in certain situations;
14 construing provisions; establishing immunity of
certain persons; amending 36 O.S. 2021, Sections
15 1901, as last amended by Section 1, Chapter 371,
O.S.L. 2023, and 1914 (36 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
16 1901), which relate to rehabilitation and
liquidation; defining terms; modifying definitions;
17 prohibiting records to be considered certain records;
prohibiting disclosure of certain records in certain
18 situations; construing provisions; allowing the
Commissioner to employ or contract with certain
19 persons; establishing certain expenses as fixed by
the Commissioner; allowing the Commissioner to audit
20 certain persons or books; establishing certain
expenses as cost of administration; construing
21 provisions; authorizing the Oklahoma Receivership
Office to deposit certain funds; allowing combining
22 of certain funds; establishing use of certain funds;
establishing certain immunity and indemnification;
