6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
7 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 36 O.S. 2021, Section 301, is
8 amended to read as follows:
9 Section 301. A. The Insurance Department of the State of
10 Oklahoma is hereby created, and shall consist of such divisions,
11 sections, bureaus, offices, and positions as may be established by
12 the Insurance Commissioner, or by law. The Insurance Commissioner
13 shall be the chief executive officer of the Insurance Department.
14 The powers and duties of the Insurance Commissioner shall be those
15 created by the Oklahoma Insurance Code. The Insurance Department
16 shall be situated in one area in the State Capitol or some other
17 location conveniently accessible to the general public subject to
18 the provisions of Sections 63 and 94 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma
19 Statutes and Section 580:20-13-5 of the Oklahoma Administrative
20 Code.
21 B. There is hereby established a division within the Department
22 to handle the administration and operation of supervisions,
23 conservatorships, and receiverships in accordance with the
24 provisions of Sections 1801 through 1938 of this title. The
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1916 Page 2

1 divi sion shall be under the direction of the Commissioner and any
2 appointed supervisor or conservator. The Commissioner shall take
3 all appropriate actions necessary to ensure a smooth conversion of
4 all existing supervisions, conservatorships, and receiverships to
5 the division by no later than January 1, 2028.
