23 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 36 O.S. 2021, Section 1804, is
24 amended to read as follows:
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1916 Page 7

1 Section 1804. A. During any period of supervision, the
2 Commissioner may appoint a supervisor for such insurer and provide
3 that the insurer may not do any of the following things without the
4 prior approval of the Commissioner or his the supervisor:
5 1. Dispose, convey or encumber any of its assets or its
6 business in force;
7 2. Withdraw funds from bank accounts;
8 3. Lend funds;
9 4. Invest funds;
10 5. Transfer property;
11 6. Incur any debt, obligation or liability;
12 7. Merge or consolidate with another company; or
13 8. Enter into any new reinsurance contract or treaty.
14 B. In addition, the Commissioner or the supervisor may require
15 of the insurer, the following:
16 1. Periodic actuarial reviews; and
17 2. That the insurer limit or cease writing certain lines of
18 insurance.
19 C. Within the limits of duties imposed upon them, appointed
20 supervisors shall possess all the powers given to a supervisor and,
21 in the exercise of those powers, shall be subject to all duties,
22 powers, and limitations imposed upon the supervisor.
