24 amended to read as follows:
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1916 Page 8

1 Section 1805. A. If, after notice and hearing, at the
2 conclusion of the 90-day ninety-day period the Insurance
3 Commissioner determines that the insurer has failed to comply with
4 his the Commissioner’s lawful requirements, or upon consent of the
5 insurer, he the Commissioner may appoint a conservator, who. Within
6 the limits of the duties imposed upon the conservator, the
7 conservator shall possess all the powers given to a conservator and,
8 in the exercise of those powers, shall be subject to all of the
9 duties, powers, and limitations imposed upon the conservator. The
10 conservator shall immediately:
11 1. Take charge of such insurer and all of the property, books,
