17 B. During the pendency of conservatorship, the conservator
18 shall make such reports as may be required by the Commissioner, and
19 may:
20 1. Take all necessary measures to preserve, protect and recover
21 any assets or property of such insurer including claims or causes of
22 action belonging to orwhich or which may be asserted by such insurer
23 in his or her own name as conservator; and
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1916 Page 9

1 2. File, prosecute and defend any legal actions which have been
2 filed, or which may thereafter be filed, by or against such insurer,
3 as he the conservator deems necessary to protect all of the
4 interested parties or any property affected thereby. The
5 conservator shall file all quarterly and annual reports required by
6 the Oklahoma Insurance Code and in the same manner as the insurer.
7 C. If upon appointment of a conservator or at any time during
8 the pendency of such conservatorship it appears that the insurer can
9 best be protected by reinsuring the same, the conservator may, with
10 the approval of the Commissioner, after appraisal of all assets of
11 the insurer:
12 1. Reinsure all or part of such insurer’s policies or
13 certificates of insurance with any solvent insurers authorized to
14 transact business in this state; and
15 2. To the extent that such insurer is possessed of reserves
16 attributable to such policies or certificates of insurance, transfer
17 to the reinsuring company such reserves or any portion thereof as
18 may be required to consummate the reinsurance of such policies,
19 which transfer of reserves shall not be deemed a preference of
20 creditors.
21 D. If the Commissioner is satisfied that the insurer is not in
