1 empl oyed by the Commissioner. The cost of such attorneys’ services
2 must shall be reasonable under the circumstances and shall be paid
3 from the assets and funds of the insurer to the Commissioner.
4 G. The Commissioner, in his or her discretion, may require
5 audits to be made of the books of any appointed supervisor or
6 conservator relating to any supervision or conservatorship
7 established under this act, and a report of each audit shall be
8 filed with the Commissioner. The books, records, and other
9 documents of the supervision or conservatorship shall be made
10 available to the auditor at any time without notice. The expenses
11 of each audit shall be considered a cost of administration of the
12 supervision or conservatorship.
13 H. The records of an insurer held by the Commissioner,
14 supervisor, conservator, and his or her employees shall not be:
15 1. Considered records of the Insurance Department;
16 2. Public records;
17 3. Subject to subpoena; and
18 4. Disclosed, except in connection with administrative or
