5 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1813 of Title 36, unless there
7 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 The Insurance Commissioner, his or her employees, current or
9 former appointed supervisor or conservator, or the supervisor’s or
10 conservator’s contractors shall:
11 1. Have no liability and no cause of action of any nature shall
12 arise against such person for any action taken in performance of his
13 or her powers and duties pursuant to this act; and
14 2. Be indemnified to the same extent as a receiver and the
15 receiver’s employees and contractors are indemnified pursuant to
16 Section 1937 of Title 36 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
